    "plan_content": "Here's the complete implementation plan for `Bun.INI`:\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n**2 new files** + **7 existing files** to modify + **1 new test file**.\n\n### New Files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `src/interchange/ini.zig` | Self-contained INI parser (does NOT use `src/ini.zig`) |\n| `src/bun.js/api/INIObject.zig` | JS binding with `parse()`, `stringify()`, `exprToJS()` |\n\n### Modified Files\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `src/interchange.zig` | Add `pub const ini = @import(\"./interchange/ini.zig\");` |\n| `src/bun.js/api.zig` | Add `pub const INIObject = @import(\"./api/INIObject.zig\");` |\n| `src/bun.js/api/BunObject.zig` | 4 insertions: lazy prop callback, `exportAll()` entry, getter fn, import alias |\n| `src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject+exports.h` | Add `macro(INI) \\` between `Glob` and `JSON5` (alphabetical) |\n| `src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject.cpp` | Add `INI  BunObject_lazyPropCb_wrap_INI  DontDelete|PropertyCallback` to hash table |\n| `src/analytics.zig` | Add `pub var ini_parse: usize = 0;` |\n| `packages/bun-types/bun.d.ts` | Add `namespace INI { parse, stringify }` after `namespace TOML` |\n\n### New Test File\n`test/js/bun/ini/ini-bun.test.ts` — avoids collision with existing `ini.test.ts` which tests the internal package-manager parser.\n\n---\n\n### Key design decisions in the plan:\n\n- **Parser** (`src/interchange/ini.zig`): Line-by-line, returns `Expr` AST. Inline `; #` comments stripped tracking quote state. Unquoted values coerced (`true`/`false`→bool, parseable→number, `null`→null). Dotted section names `[a.b.c]` create deep nesting. \n- **`stringify()`**: Two `StringBuilder` buffers (scalars first, then `[sections]`), concatenated — ensures valid INI output order. Throws on depth > 2 or circular refs.\n- **`exprToJS()`**: Local copy following the JSON5Object pattern (each format object keeps its own).\n- **Test file name**: `ini-bun.test.ts` to avoid conflicts with the existing `ini.test.ts`.",
